                        in red.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin change="#fix-dates">undated</origin>
                  <provenance when="1891">Bought by <persName key="" role="fmo">Sheykh A-</persName> for 63
                     francs from a Bábí who was returning to <placeName>Persia</placeName>, and sent
                     on to <persName xml:lang="en" type="standard" key="person_29651479"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/29651479/" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">E.
                        G. Browne</persName> in <placeName key="place_7002473"
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7002473">Constantinople</placeName> in
                     <date when="1891-08">August 1891</date>. Sheykh A-'s covering letter, itemizing
                     the cost (30 folios at two francs each, plus binding), is quoted by Browne in
                     Persian and English translation.</provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1936">Passed to <placeName>Cambridge</placeName> University
                     Library in <date when="1936">1936</date> (the "Browne
                     Bequest").</acquisition>
               </history>
